CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 4, 1954, pg. 1 reads: "3rd Prize - Darryl Francis Pennywell, 20 1/2 pounds, 30 1/2 inches tall, son of Mr. and Mrs. Clarence and Mary Ellen Pennywell, 239 Bonifay Street, is shown with his father as he received check for $25. Babies were given numbers.  No names or addresses were used or known throughout the examinations by Carnation Milk Company's board of judges which included doctors and social workers."
TitMainTitle: John Ruffing Jr. presenting third prize to Darryl Francis Pennywell, son of Clarence Pennywell, in Centre Avenue YMCA during Carnation Milk baby contest
